news.title: RBI allows home loan disbursals sanctioned before Oct 20: Navi Finserv
news.para: ​Earlier this month, the RBI had ordered Navi Finserv to cease and desist from sanctioning and disbursing loans effective from the close of business of October 21 on material supervisory concerns, including usurious pricing.

news.title: EFC (I) receives approval for its small & medium REIT
news.para: EFC (I)'s small & medium real estate investment trust namely Emberstone SM REIT will be eligible to make an initial offer for units of its first scheme for an amount of up to Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Somany Ceramics' net profit dips 41.28% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Somany Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 667.65 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 1.31 per cent from Rs 659 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop six acres land in Pune
news.para: Shriram Properties is targeting to launch this project during H2 FY25. It has aggregate revenue potential of approximately Rs 700-750 crore.

news.title: Norway's sovereign wealth fund acquires 98% stake in Menlo Park office property for $217 million
news.para: Norges Bank Investment Management (NBIM), the world's largest sovereign wealth fund, said it bought the stake from a joint venture between Clarion Partners and Invesco Real Estate.

news.title: Singapore's Hongkong Land to wind down build-to-sell division
news.para: Hongkong Land, which expects to raise proceeds worth $6 billion from the divestment, said the new plan will leverage its established flagship prime mixed-use projects in Hong Kong, Singapore and Shanghai.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 23.13 crore worth of properties in Punjab in PMLA case against Hacienda Projects
news.para: ED attached five immovable properties worth Rs 23.13 crore in the form of agricultural land and industrial plots at Hoshiarpur, Fatehgarh Sahib and Mohali, Punjab in the name of Moonlight Propbuild Pvt Ltd and Elco Global Ventures LLP

news.title: Group of ministers propose raising affordable housing threshold to Rs 55 lakh
news.para: Currently affordable housing attracts GST of 1%, while other housing projects are levied 5%. The input tax credit (ITC) facility is not available in both cases.

news.title: China's Sino-Ocean to issue $4 billion in convertible bonds to creditors
news.para: This issuance, along with new debts worth $2.2 billion, forms a part of the indebted developer's $5.64 billion offshore debt restructuring plan as it attempts to raise funds to repay its creditors.

news.title: Mysuru development body transfers maintenance of approved layouts to local bodies
news.para: A decision in this regard was taken in a meeting chaired by Muda chairman G Lakshmikantha Reddy, who is also the Mysuru DC.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government plans to expedite new airport work in Nellore district
news.para: The govt had already identified about 1,379 acres of land for the airport. However, part of the land is yet to be acquired. The district administration has started the initiated the process to acquire the remaining land following the instructions from chief secretary.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body and IFC working on 'green city' action plan
news.para: The GCAP aims to mainstream the climate mitigation lens within the GVMC's Eco-Vizag campaign by identifying a roadmap to help Vizag meet its vision for the environment and development.

news.title: Telangana government creates 25 urban development bodies for infrastructure growth
news.para: The newly created areas include Adilabad, Jogulamba Gadwal, Kagaznagar, Kothagudem, Mahabubabad, Mancherial, Nagarkurnool, Nirmal, Kamareddy, Suryapet, Wanaparthy, Narayanpet, Jagtial, Medak, Yadadri-Bhongiri, Jayashankar Bhupalapally, Sangareddy, Nalgonda, Vikarabad and Jangaon.

news.title: Indore civic body allocates 8.5 hectares of land in Limbodagari and Palakhedi under PMAY 2.0
news.para: "Following this, a request was placed before the district administration, and Collector Asheesh Singh allotted 4.892 hectares of land in Limbodagari and 3.764 hectares in Palakhedi for the PMAY 2.0 housing scheme," said  IMC Commissioner.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance to raise $125 million via ECBs
news.para: PNB Housing expects to start corporate business in the next few months to further help in yield and retail business.

news.title: Bhutani Infra's Sancoale project exposes all that’s wrong with Goa planning: GBA
news.para: GBA has also come out in support of former sarpanch Premanand Naik, who is on a hunger strike until the permissions are revoked. “There will be no light for Goa if this game of land conversions and bypassing of building regulations continue,” said GBA secretary Reboni Saha.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder buys Sabarmati riverfront plot for Rs 156.13 crore
news.para: The successful bidder, a leading Mumbai-based real estate company, will now develop a mixed-use commercial building spanning 60,050 sq m, housing upscale offices, co-working spaces, restaurants, retail stores, lounges and a food court.

news.title: Noida authority approves reallocation of data centre plots to IT and ITES sector
news.para: In 2022, on the heels of the Global Investor Summit, the land parcels, spanning over 29,000 sqm, was offered for setting up data centre units under the UP data centre policy, 2021.

news.title: Adani Cement targets 140 MTPA capacity by FY28
news.para: Ambuja Cement, part of Adani Group, which houses all cement assets, is a debt-free company and as of September 2024, cash and cash equivalent for the company was at Rs 10,135 crore, said Kapur.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects acquires 17.45 acres land in Bengaluru for Rs 462 crore
news.para: The acquired land will be planned for residential development spanning approximately 2.68 million sq ft of developable area.
